oup D]])\n|-\n|{{flagicon|CUB}} [[Cuba]]\n|Yadel Mart\u00ednez\n|{{flagicon|CAN}} Joe Fletcher<br />{{flagicon|PAR}} Dar\u00edo Gaona\n|[[Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario Group C#Mexico vs Venezuela|Mexico\u2013Venezuela]] ([[Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario Group C|Group C]])\n|-\n|{{flagicon|ECU}} [[Ecuador]]\n|[[Roddy Zambrano]]\n|Luis Vera<br />Byron Romero\n|[[Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario Group A#United States vs Costa Rica|United States\u2013Costa Rica]] ([[Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario Group A|Group A]])<br />[[Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario Group D#Chile vs Panama|Chile\u2013Panama]] ([[Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario Group D|Group D]])\n|-\n|{{flagicon|SLV}} [[El Salvador]]\n|[[Joel Aguilar]]\n|Juan Zumba<br />William Torres\n|[[Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario Group D#Argentina vs Panama|Argentina\u2013Panama]] ([[Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario Group D|Group D]])<br />[[Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario knockout stage#Colombia vs Chile|Colombia\u2013Chile]] ([[Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario#Semi-finals|Semi-finals]])\n|-\n|{{flagicon|MEX}} [[Mexico]]\n|[[Roberto Garc\u00eda Orozco]]\n|Jos\u00e9 Luis Camargo<br />Alberto Mor\u00edn\n|[[Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario Group A#United States vs Colombia|United States\u2013Colombia]] ([[Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario Group A|Group A]])<br />[[Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario knockout stage#Argentina vs Venezuela|Argentina\u2013Venezuela]] ([[Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario#Quarter-finals|Quarter-finals]])\n|-\n|{{flagicon|PAN}} [[Panama]]\n|[[Jhon Pitti]]\n|Gabriel Victoria<br />{{flagicon|HON}} Cristian Ram\u00edrez\n|[[Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario Group B#Haiti vs Peru|Haiti\u2013Peru]] ([[Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario Group B|Group B]])\n|-\n|{{flagicon|PAR}} [[Paraguay]]\n|[[Enrique C\u00e1ceres]]\n|Eduardo Cardozo<br />Milciades Sald\u00edvar\n|[[Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario Group C#Mexico vs Uruguay|Mexico\u2013Uruguay]] ([[Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario Group C|Group C]])<br/ >[[Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario knockout stage#United States vs Argentina|United States\u2013Argentina]] ([[Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario#Semi-finals|Semi-finals]])\n|-\n|{{flagicon|PER}} [[Peru]]\n|[[V\u00edctor Carrillo]]\n|Jorge Luis Yupanqui Namuche<br />Coty Carrera\n|[[Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario Group C#Jamaica vs Venezuela|Jamaica\u2013Venezuela]] ([[Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario Group C|Group C]])<br />[[Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario Group D#Argentina vs Bolivia|Argentina\u2013Bolivia]] ([[Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario Group D|Group D]])\n|-\n|{{flagicon|USA}} [[United States]]\n|[[Mark Geiger]]\n|Charles Morgante<br />{{flagicon|CAN}} Joe Fletcher\n|[[Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario Group B#Brazil vs Haiti|Brazil\u2013Haiti]] ([[Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario Group B|Group B]])\n|-\n|{{flagicon|USA}} [[United States]]\n|[[Jair Marrufo]]\n|Peter Manikowski<br />Corey Rockwell\n|[[Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario Group D#Chile vs Bolivia|Chile\u2013Bolivia]] ([[Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario Group D|Group D]])\n|-\n|{{flagicon|URU}} [[Uruguay]]\n|[[Daniel Fedorczuk]]\n|Nicol\u00e1s Taran<br />Richard Trinidad\n|[[Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario Group D#Argentina vs Chile|Argentina\u2013Chile]] ([[Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario Group D|Group D]])<br/ >[[Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario knockout stage#United States vs Colombia|United States\u2013Colombia]] ([[Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario#Third place play-off|Third place play-off]])\n|-\n|{{flagicon|URU}} [[Uruguay]]\n|[[Andr\u00e9s Cunha]]\n|Nicol\u00e1s Taran<br />Richard Trinidad\n|[[Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario Group B#Brazil vs Peru|Brazil\u2013Peru]] ([[Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario Group B|Group B]])\n|-\n|{{flagicon|VEN}} [[Venezuela]]\n|[[Jos\u00e9 Argote]]\n|Luis Murillo<br />Luis Alfonso S\u00e1nchez P\u00e9rez\n|[[Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario Group A#Colombia vs Costa Rica|Colombia\u2013Costa Rica]] ([[Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario Group A|Group A]])\n|}\n\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! width=140 | Country !! width=200 | Fourth official\n|-\n| {{flagicon|BRA}} [[Brazil]] || [[Wilton Sampaio]]\n|-\n| {{flagicon|COL}} [[Colombia]] || Wilson Lamouroux\n|-\n| {{flagicon|USA}} [[United States]] || Armando Villarreal\n|-\n| {{flagicon|URU}} [[Uruguay]] || [[Daniel Fedorczuk]]\n|}\n{{col-2}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! width=160 | Country !! width=200 | Reserve assistant referee\n|-\n| {{flagicon|ARG}} [[Argentina]] || Gustavo Fabi\u00e1n Rossi Fagivoli\n|-\n| {{flagicon|COL}} [[Colombia]]|| John Alexander Le\u00f3n S\u00e1nchez\n|-\n| {{flagicon|PAR}} [[Paraguay]] || Dar\u00edo Antonio Gaona Rodr\u00edguez\n|-\n| {{flagicon|USA}} [[United States]] || Corey Parker\n|}\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Opening ceremony==\nThe opening ceremony of Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario took place at [[Levi's Stadium]] in [[Santa Clara, California|Santa Clara]] 21:00 [[Eastern Time Zone|EDT]] ([[UTC\u221204:00|UTC\u22124]]) on 3 June 2016 ahead of the opening match and featured musical performances by Colombian singer [[J Balvin]], [[United States|American]] singer [[Jason Derulo]] and the Canadian band [[Magic!]]<ref>{{cite web|title=2016 COPA AMERICA CENTENARIO WILL KICK OFF WITH THE HOTTEST SONGS OF THE SUMMER BEFORE OPENING MATCH|url=http://www.ca2016.com/article/2016-copa-america-centenario-will-kick-off-with-the-hottest-songs-of-the-summer-before-opening-match#sf26578015|work=Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario|location=Chicago|date=19 May 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Group stage==\n[[File:Copa America Centenario Map.svg|thumb|250px|right|{{Legend|#b74A54|Group stage}}\n{{Legend|#e4e454|Quarter-finals}}\n{{Legend|#81c846|Fourth place}}\n{{Legend|#269c5a|Third place}}\n{{Legend|#34c0be|Runner-up}}\n{{Legend|#2b42a3|Champion}}]]\nAll times are [[Eastern Time Zone|EDT]] ([[UTC\u221204:00|UTC\u22124]]). The top two teams from each group advanced to the quarter-finals.\n\n===Tiebreakers===\nThe ranking of each team in each group was determined as follows:<ref name=\"regulations\"/>\n#Greatest number of points obtained in all group matches\n#Goal difference in all group matches\n#Greatest number of goals scored in all group matches\n#If two or more teams were equal on the basis of the above three criteria, their rankings would further be determined as follows:\n##Greatest number of points obtained in the group matches between the teams concerned\n##Goal difference resulting from the group matches between the teams concerned\n##Greater number of goals scored in all group matches between the teams concerned\n##Drawing of lots\n\n===Group A===\n{{main|Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario Group A}}\n{{Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario group tables|Group A|only_pld_pts=no_hide_class_rules}}\n\n{{#lst:Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario Group A|m1}}\n{{#lst:Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario Group A|m2}}\n----\n{{#lst:Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario Group A|m9}}\n{{#lst:Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario Group A|m10}}\n----\n{{#lst:Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario Group A|m17}}\n{{#lst:Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario Group A|m18}}\n\n===Group B===\n{{main|Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario Group B}}\n{{Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario group tables|Group B|only_pld_pts=no_hide_class_rules}}\n\n{{#lst:Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario Group B|m3}}\n{{#lst:Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario Group B|m4}}\n----\n{{#lst:Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario Group B|m11}}\n{{#lst:Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario Group B|m12}}\n----\n{{#lst:Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario Group B|m19}}\n{{#lst:Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario Group B|m20}}\n\n===Group C===\n{{main|Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario Group C}}\n{{Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario group tables|Group C|only_pld_pts=no_hide_class_rules}}\n\n{{#lst:Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario Group C|m5}}\n{{#lst:Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario Group C|m6}}\n----\n{{#lst:Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario Group C|m13}}\n{{#lst:Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario Group C|m14}}\n----\n{{#lst:Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario Group C|m21}}\n{{#lst:Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario Group C|m22}}\n\n===Group D===\n{{main|Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario Group D}}\n{{Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario group tables|Group D|only_pld_pts=no_hide_class_rules}}\n\n{{#lst:Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario Group D|m7}}\n{{#lst:Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario Group D|m8}}\n----\n{{#lst:Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario Group D|m15}}\n{{#lst:Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario Group D|m16}}\n----\n{{#lst:Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario Group D|m23}}\n{{#lst:Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario Group D|m24}}\n\n==Knockout stage==\n{{main|Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario knockout stage}}\n\nAll times are [[Eastern Time Zone|EDT]] ([[UTC\u221204:00|UTC\u22124]]). In the quarter-finals, semi-finals, and third place match of the knockout stage, a [[penalty shoot-out (association football)|penalty shoot-out]] was used to decide the winner if tied after 90 minutes. In the final, [[Overtime (sports)#Association football|extra time]] and a [[penalty shoot-out (association football)|penalty shoot-out]] was used to decide the winner if necessary.<ref name=\"regulations\"/> Should the final enter extra time, a fourth substitute would be allowed as part of FIFA's approval of rule changes based on [[International Football Association Board|IFAB]]'s new regulations, however neither teams in the final ended up taking advantage of this rule.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ca2016.com/article/copa-america-centenario-local-organizing-committee-announces-revised-game-regulations|title=Copa America Centenario To Be First Around The World To Implement New Regulations Based On 2016/2017 Laws Of The Game|publisher=Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario|date=3 June 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Bracket===\n{{#lst:Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario knockout stage|bracket}}\n\n===Quarter-finals===\n{{#lst:Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario knockout stage|m25}}\n----\n{{#lst:Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario knockout stage|m26}}\n----\n{{#lst:Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario knockout stage|m27}}\n----\n{{#lst:Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario knockout stage|m28}}\n\n===Semi-finals===\n{{#lst:Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario knockout stage|m29}}\n----\n{{#lst:Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario knockout stage|m30}}\n\n===Third place play-off===\n{{#lst:Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario knockout stage|m31}}\n\n===Final===\n{{main|Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario Final}}\n\n{{#lst:Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario Final|m32}}\n\n==Statistics==\n{{Details|Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario statistics}}\n\n===Goalscorers===\nChile's Eduardo Vargas received the Golden Boot award for scoring six goals. In total, 91 goals were scored by 62 different players, with three of them credited as own goals.\n\n<!-- Alphabetical by country AND player-->\n;6 goals\n{{Div col|colwidth=22em}}\n*{{flagicon|CHI}} [[Eduardo Vargas]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n;5 goals\n{{Div col|colwidth=22em}}\n*{{flagicon|ARG}} [[Lionel Messi]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n;4 goals\n{{Div col|colwidth=22em}}\n*{{flagicon|ARG}} [[Gonzalo Higua\u00edn]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n;3 goals\n{{Div col|colwidth=22em}}\n<!-- Do NOT change until the final whistle of match -->\n*{{flagicon|BRA}} [[Philippe Coutinho]]\n*{{flagicon|CHI}} [[Alexis S\u00e1nchez]]\n*{{flagicon|USA}} [[Clint Dempsey]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n;2 goals\n{{Div col|colwidth=22em}}\n*{{flagicon|ARG}} [[Ezequiel Lavezzi]]\n*{{flagicon|ARG}} [[Erik Lamela]]\n*{{flagicon|BRA}} [[Renato Augusto]]\n*{{flagicon|CHI}} [[Jos\u00e9 Pedro Fuenzalida]]\n*{{flagicon|CHI}} [[Edson Puch]]\n*{{flagicon|CHI}} [[Arturo Vidal]]\n*{{flagicon|COL}} [[Carlos Bacca]]\n*{{flagicon|COL}} [[James Rodr\u00edguez]]\n*{{flagicon|ECU}} [[Enner Valencia]]\n*{{flagicon|PAN}} [[Blas P\u00e9rez]]\n*{{flagicon|VEN}} [[Jos\u00e9 Salom\u00f3n Rond\u00f3n|Salom\u00f3n Rond\u00f3n]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n;1 goal\n{{Div col|colwidth=22em}}\n*{{flagicon|ARG}} [[Sergio Ag\u00fcero]]\n*{{flagicon|ARG}} [[\u00c9ver Banega]]\n*{{flagicon|ARG}} [[V\u00edctor Cuesta]]\n*{{flagicon|ARG}} [[\u00c1ngel Di Mar\u00eda]]\n*{{flagicon|ARG}} [[Nicol\u00e1s Otamendi]]\n*{{flagicon|BOL}} [[Juan Carlos Arce]]\n*{{flagicon|BOL}} [[Jhasmani Campos]]\n*{{flagicon|BRA}} [[Gabriel Barbosa|Gabriel]]\n*{{flagicon|BRA}} [[Lucas Lima]]\n*{{flagicon|CHI}} [[Charles Ar\u00e1nguiz